NAME
	member_array - see if an element is a member of an array

SYNOPSIS
	int member_array(mixed item, mixed *arr)

DESCRIPTION
	Checks of 'item' is a member of the array 'arr'.

RETURN VALUE
	Returns the index of the first occurrence of item in array arr.
	If not found, then -1 is returned.

EXAMPLES
	mixed *arr;
	int x;

	x = member_array("STR", arr);
	if (x > -1) {
	   write("Found STR: " + x + "\n");
	}

SEE ALSO
	afun/call_array, afun/filter_array, afun/filter_mapping,
	afun/map_array, safun/member_map, safun/random_element,
	safun/split_array, safun/uniq_array
